Problem 6Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 6

::dia(#ch6_1_dia16) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G1 ab="F2 G1 G2 H3 J1 J2" aw="E2 F1 F3 G3 H1 H2"
Correct Answer

By playing 1, Black can capture two white stones.

::dia(#ch6_1_dia17) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="F7 G7 H8 J6 J7" aw="E7 F6 F8 G6 G8 H6 H7"
If White Plays First

If it’s White’s turn to play, he will capture two stones with 1.

::h2
Problem 7

::dia(#ch6_1_dia18) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F6F5N13E6 ab="D6 E5 E6 E7 F4 F7 G5 G6 N13" aw="D7 D8 E8 F5 F6 F8 G7"
Problem 7Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 7

::dia(#ch6_1_dia19) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E8 ab="D8 E7 E8 E9 F6 F9 G7 G8" aw="D10 D9 E10 F10 F7 F8 G9"
Correct Answer

By playing 1, Black can capture two white stones.

::dia(#ch6_1_dia20) sz=13 vw=A5H13 base=none at=1 mv=E8 ab="D8 E7 E9 F6 F9 G7 G8" aw="D10 D9 E10 E8 F10 F7 F8 G9"
If White Plays First

If it’s White’s turn, it is White who will capture two stones.

::h2
