::chapter(#ch6_2)

::h3
How to Save Endangered Stones

::h2
Problem 15

::dia(#ch6_2_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13K3 ab="K2 K3 K4 L3 N13" aw="J4 K5 L4"
Problem 15Black to play

How can Black save his endangered stone?

::h3
Answer 15

::dia(#ch6_2_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=K5 ab="K4 K5 K6 L5" aw="J6 K7 L6"
Correct Answer

Black can save his stone by connecting with 1.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia2) sz=13 vw=A5H13 base=none at=1 mv=E10G10E9 ab="E10 E8 F9 G10" aw="D10 E11 E9 F10"
Wrong Answer

If Black threatens to capture a white stone by playing at 1, White captures a black stone with 2.

::h2
Problem 16

::dia(#ch6_2_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13E8 ab="D8 E7 E8 E9 F5 N13" aw="C8 D6 D7 D9"
Problem 16Black to play

One black stone is about to be captured. How can Black save it?

::h3
Answer 16

::dia(#ch6_2_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E10 ab="D10 E10 E11 E9 F7" aw="C10 D11 D8 D9"
Correct Answer

Black can save his stone by connecting with 1.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia5) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=D10C11E10 ab="C11 D10 E11 E9 F7" aw="C10 D11 D8 D9 E10"
Wrong Answer

If Black threatens to capture a white stone by playing 1, White captures a black stone with 2.

::h2
Problem 17

::dia(#ch6_2_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13L5 ab="H5 K5 L4 L5 L6 M6 N13" aw="K6 L7 M5 M7 N6"
Problem 17Black to play

Two black stones are in danger. How can Black save them?

::h3
Answer 17

::dia(#ch6_2_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=L7 ab="H7 K7 L6 L7 L8 M8" aw="K8 L9 M7 M9 N8"
Correct Answer

Black can save his two stones by connecting at 1.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia8) sz=13 vw=A1H13 base=none at=1 mv=F8G8D8F7 ab="C7 D8 E7 F6 F8 G8" aw="E8 F7 F9 G7 G9 H8"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White will capture two black stones with 2.

The following sample problems are out of sequence to give you more of a flavor of the difficulty of the book.

::h2
Problem 25

::dia(#ch6_2_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13F7 ab="B8 C8 D7 D9 E9 F7 F9 G8 N13" aw="B9 C6 C7 C9 D8 E8 F6 F8"
Problem 25Black to play

How should Black atari the three white stones?

::h3
Answer 25

::dia(#ch6_2_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9 ab="B10 C10 D11 D9 E11 F11 F9 G10" aw="B11 C11 C8 C9 D10 E10 F10 F8"
Correct Answer

Black can capture three stones with an atari at 1.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=E9F9 ab="B10 C10 D11 D9 E11 E9 F11 G10" aw="B11 C11 C8 C9 D10 E10 F10 F8 F9"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White plays 2 and his stones cannot be captured.

::h2
Problem 60

::dia(#ch6_2_dia12) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13D7 ab="A8 A9 B6 B8 C2 C3 C4 C6 C7 D1 D2 D4 D5 D6 D7 E1 E11 F10 F11 F8 F9 G7 H7 J6 J7 J9 K6 L5 L6 L9 M6 M8 N13 N7" aw="A10 B9 C10 C8 C9 D11 D3 D9 E1 E10 E2 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F7 G1 G6 H5 H6 J5 K2 K4 L1 L4 M4 M5 N5 N6"
Problem 60Black to play

Where is the last point of profit?

::h3
Answer 60

::dia(#ch6_2_dia13) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D9 ab="A10 A11 B10 B8 C4 C5 C6 C8 C9 D1 D2 D3 D4 D6 D7 D8 D9 E13 E2 F10 F11 F12 F13 G9 H9 J11 J8 J9 K8 L11 L7 L8 M10 M8 N9" aw="A12 B11 C10 C11 C12 D11 D13 D5 E1 E10 E11 E12 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F2 F9 G3 G8 H7 H8 J7 K4 K6 L3 L6 M6 M7 N7 N8"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the last point of profit left.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia14) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=K7D9 ab="A10 A11 B10 B8 C4 C5 C6 C8 C9 D1 D2 D3 D4 D6 D7 D8 E13 E2 F10 F11 F12 F13 G9 H9 J11 J8 J9 K7 K8 L11 L7 L8 M10 M8 N9" aw="A12 B11 C10 C11 C12 D11 D13 D5 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F2 F9 G3 G8 H7 H8 J7 K4 K6 L3 L6 M6 M7 N7 N8"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 is on a neutral point. White 2 takes the last profitable point. Black has lost a point.

::h2
Problem 72

::dia(#ch6_2_dia15) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G4 ab="F2 F4 F5 G1 G2 G3 G4 G6 H4 H6 J4 J6 K5 L5 N13" aw="E2 E3 F1 F3 G1 H1 H2 H3 H5 J3 J5 K4"
Problem 72Black to play

How should Black answer White 1?

::h3
Answer 72

::dia(#ch6_2_dia16) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="F4 F6 F7 G3 G4 G5 G6 G8 H6 H8 J6 J8 K7 L7" aw="E4 E5 F3 F5 G2 H3 H4 H5 H7 J5 J7 K6"
Correct Answer

Black should play 1, connecting his four stones in atari to the ones above.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia17) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H7J7G5F4G4G3G7G6 ab="F4 F6 F7 G3 G4 G5 G7 G8 H6 H8 J6 J8 K7 L7" aw="E4 E5 F3 F5 G2 G6 H3 H4 H5 H7 J5 J7 K6"
Wrong Answer

If Black captures two stones with 1, White captures four stones with 2.

::h2
Problem 136

::dia(#ch6_2_dia18) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13F4 ab="D4 D5 D6 E3 E7 F3 F7 G2 G5 G7 H2 H6 J2 J6 K3 K4 K5" aw="E5 F4 F6 G3 G4 G6 H3 H5 J4 J5 N13"
Problem 136White to play

Where does White play to live?

::h3
Answer 136

::dia(#ch6_2_dia19) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F6 ab="D6 D7 D8 E5 E9 F5 F9 G4 G7 G9 H4 H8 J4 J8 K5 K6 K7" aw="E7 F6 F8 G5 G6 G8 H5 H7 J6 J7"
Correct Answer

White 1 is the vital point. White has two distinct eyes and cannot be killed.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia20) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G7F7F6 ab="D6 D7 D8 E5 E9 F5 F6 F9 G4 G7 G9 H4 H8 J4 J8 K5 K6 K7" aw="E7 F7 F8 G5 G6 G8 H5 H7 J6 J7"
Wrong Answer

If White captures a stone with 1, Black 2 leaves White with only one real eye, so he is dead.

::h2
Problem 207

::dia(#ch6_2_dia21) sz=13 vw=C1N11 base=none at=1 mv=N11J9N11H9F9 ab="F8 F9 G8 H7 J7 J9 K7 K8 N11" aw="E7 F7 G7 G9 H8 H9 J8 K9 L7 L8 N11"
Problem 207Black to play

Capture three white stones with the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3
Answer 207

::dia(#ch6_2_dia22) sz=13 vw=C1N11 base=none at=1 mv=J11H11F11 ab="F10 F11 G10 H9 J11 J9 K10 K9" aw="E9 F9 G11 G9 H10 H11 J10 K11 L10 L9"
Correct Answer

Black sacrifices a stone with 1, then plays 3. White can’t connect, so he has lost four stones.

::dia(#ch6_2_dia23) sz=13 vw=C1N11 base=none at=1 mv=F11J11 ab="F10 F11 G10 H9 J9 K10 K9" aw="E9 F9 G11 G9 H10 J10 J11 K11 L10 L9"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1 first, he fails. White connects with 2 and his stones are safe.

